<div class="page-header">
  <h1>About BCGMN</h1>
</div>

<div class="about-body">

  <section class="about-section">
    <p>The Backgammon Club of the Great Manhattan North is a competitive backgammon club in the Washington Heights neighborhood of Manhattan in New York City. We welcome players of all levels who share a love of the game.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>Where &amp; When</h2>
    <p><a href="https://www.lecheilebarnyc.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Le Chéile</a> &mdash; 839 W 181st St in Manhattan (take A train to 181st).
    </p>
    <p>We meet on the second floor of the restaurant.</p>
    <p class="about-times"><span>Registration</span> 7:00 pm &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; <span>Play begins</span> 7:30 pm</p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>House Rules</h2>
    <p>Each meeting is a 3-round Swiss tournament &mdash; everyone plays all three rounds regardless of wins or losses, with pairings based on similar records. A bye is assigned when there's an odd number of players. We play under <a href="https://usbgf.org/tournament-rules/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">USBGF rules</a> with the following specifics and exceptions:</p>
    <ul class="about-rules">
      <li>7-point matches</li>
      <li>Clocks are required &mdash; 12:30 per player with a 12-second delay per move</li>
      <li>We use the <strong>Dice on Checkers</strong> policy &mdash; dice landing on flat checkers (no finger dishes) are valid and must be played; if a die lands on a non-flat checker, both dice must be re-rolled.</li>
      <li>We use the <strong>Legal Moves</strong> policy &mdash; illegal checker moves must be corrected if noticed before the opponent has made a valid roll; once the opponent rolls, the move stands. Each player is obligated to report any observed illegal move, regardless of who is on roll; failing to do so is tantamount to cheating.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>BMAB</h2>
    <p>BCGMN tournaments are valid <a href="https://bgmastersab.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BMAB</a> entries. The Backgammon Masters Awarding Body awards mastership titles to players based on their performance rating (PR) across verified tournament matches &mdash; submitting your results is how you earn titles like Master and Grandmaster.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>How Standings Work</h2>
    <p>Points are awarded per meeting and standings reflect the current calendar year only.</p>
    <table class="about-points-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Event</th>
          <th>Points</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Attending a meeting</td><td>5</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Each match win</td><td>5</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Bye</td><td>2.5</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Going 3&ndash;0 (bonus)</td><td>5, split among all 3&ndash;0 finishers</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>Entry &amp; Prizes</h2>
    <p>There is a $20 buy-in per meeting, plus an optional $10 sidepool. Of the $20: $10 goes to the night's pool, $5 goes to the end-of-year pool (awarded to the top player in the annual standings), and $5 goes to the venue.</p>
    <p>The night's pool is split equally among all players who finish 3&ndash;0. The sidepool is split equally among sidepool participants with the best record on the night.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>Merch</h2>
    <p>Rep the club — hats, t-shirts, and more are available at <a href="{{ site.merch }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Backgammon Wizard</a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>Join Us</h2>
    <p>No advance signup required, but a quick <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">email</a> to let us know you're coming is appreciated &mdash; it helps us get an accurate headcount.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>Play Us Online</h2>
    <p>Several of our members play on <a href="https://www.opengammon.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenGammon</a> and enjoy the chance to play against people they know. If you'd like to join us, our handles are listed on the <a href="{{ '/members/' | url }}">Players page</a>. If you do join, you can ask peanut to add you to the NYC club on OpenGammon.</p>
  </section>

</div>
